                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17940716-54-off268 t17940716-54-cd269"></join>, a certain promissory note for the payment of five guineas
            </rs>; the tenor of which is in the words and figures following: No. 4760. 5l. 5s. Plymouth, 3d February 1794,</p>
               <p>I promise to pay to bearer, on demand. here, or at Messrs. Taylor, Lloyd, Bowman and Co. bankers, London, five guineas, value received.</p>
               <p>Five guineas. J. Sanders. 
